OL,6,F"In our judgment, SIAC was entitled to
OL,7,Ffind, as the specialist tribunal
OL,8,Festablished by Parliament, that the
OL,9,Fissue of whether and to what extent Ms
OL,10,FBegum's travel to Syria had been
OL,11,Fvoluntary was within the expertise of
OL,12,Fthe intelligence agencies advising the
OL,13,FSecretary of State.
OL,15,F"Ms Begum may well have been
OL,16,Finfluenced and manipulated by others
OL,17,Fbut still have made a calculated
OL,18,Fdecision to travel to Syria and align
OL,19,Fwith Isil," Baroness Carr added.
